   "body" : "The Python3 standard library method `random.sample` has the exact same functionality as the helper method `rand_keys(...)` (that is, random sampling without replacement) on a generic set or sequence, i.e. we can simply replace it. See https://docs.python.org/3/library/random.html#random.sample\r\nNote that this is also safer: in case that the sample size `k` is larger than the population count, `random.sample` throws an error:\r\n```\r\n$ python3\r\nPython 3.8.12 (default, Sep 26 2021, 13:12:50)\r\n[Clang 11.1.0 ] on openbsd7\r\nType \"help\", \"copyright\", \"credits\" or \"license\" for more information.\r\n>>> import random\r\n>>> random.sample([23, 42], 3)\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.8/random.py\", line 363, in sample\r\n    raise ValueError(\"Sample larger than population or is negative\")\r\nValueError: Sample larger than population or is negative\r\n```\r\nwhile the custom method would get stuck in an endless loop.",
   "closed_at" : "2022-03-08T14:02:50Z",
